goals.1: Identify the BGP that connect an archaeological site to the country, the continent, and the culture
goals.2: Identify the BGP to retrieve other types of an archaeological site, e.g., human settlement or theatre
goals.3: Is there any relevant numerical attribute that describes these sites, e.g., number visitors?
goals.4: Analyze the number of archaeological sites per type and country
goals.4.1: Which country has more archaeological sites? Which country has the most  human settlements?
goals.4.2: Which countries have Ancient Rome sites, which other "archaeological cultures" are described?
goals.4.3: Which country has the most diverse set of civilizations or cultures across its sites?
goals.4.4: If you are interested in visiting some sites, which country would you pick? Based on what criteria?

search_workflow.narrative: let's find properties relative to continent, culture for an archeological site
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?site ?property ?object . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, '.*(culture|continent).*', 'i') }} limit 20

search_workflow.narrative:
Point 1. Identify the BGP that connets an arch site to the country, the continent, the culture
first of all let's find an archeological site
search_workflow.query: select ?site ?name where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?site <http://schema.org/name> ?name . ?site wdt:P17 wd:Q38 . }} limit 10
output: Excavation at Largo Perosi - Via Giulia (Rome)

search_workflow.narrative: let's answer to point 1
search_workflow.query: select ?siteName ?countryName ?continent ?continentName where{{ wd:Q17631557 wdt:P17 ?country ; wdt:P30 ?continent ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName . ?continent <http://schema.org/name> ?continentName . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . }}

search_workflow.narrative: what property is Gymnasium missing?
search_workflow.query: select ?p ?name where{{ wd:Q17631557 ?p ?o . ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}

search_workflow.narrative: is a country connected to its continent via the "continent" property?
search_workflow.query: select ?continent ?name where{{ wd:Q38 wdt:P30 ?continent . ?continent <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}

select ?siteName ?countryName ?continent ?continentName ?culture ?cultureName where{{ wd:Q17631557 wdt:P17 ?country ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName ; wdt:P2596 ?culture . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName ; wdt:P30 ?continent . ?continent <http://schema.org/name> ?continentName . ?culture <http://schema.org/name> ?cultureName }}

search_workflow.narrative: what are the top 10 cultures for archeological sites in italy?
search_workflow.query: select ?cultureName (count(*) as ?n) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P2596 ?culture ; wdt:P17 wd:Q38 . ?culture <http://schema.org/name> ?cultureName }} group by ?cultureName order by desc(?n) limit 10

search_workflow.narrative: is Archeological Site a sublclass of something?
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?className where{{ wd:Q839954 wdt:P279 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's keep going
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?className where{{ wd:Q15642541 wdt:P279 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . }}
select distinct ?class ?className where{{ wd:Q1496967 wdt:P279 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . }}
select distinct ?class ?className where{{ wd:Q618123 wdt:P279 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
we're getting more and more general but i'm afraid of the amount of results i'd get if i tried to find all the subclasses of
geographic location or geographic entity.
we have already available a theatre and a city, let's check their classes
search_workflow.query: select ?class ?name where{{ wd:Q641556 wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's see the class of "ancient roman structure"
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?className where{{ wd:Q14752696 wdt:P279 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?className . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
Roman archeological structure is most likely subclass of archeological structure, for now let's check something else
does Verona Arena have a culture associated?
search_workflow.query: select ?culture ?name where{{ wd:Q641556 wdt:P2596 ?culture . ?culture <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's try and find the class related to culture
search_workflow.query: select ?class ?name where{{ wd:Q1747689 wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's find the class of all entities that refer to a certain culture
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?name where{{ ?entity wdt:P2596 ?culture . ?entity wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }} limit 100

search_workflow.narrative: what if we look for all the classes of entities that are also archeological sites?
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?name where{{ ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?entity wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }} limit 50

search_workflow.narrative: what if we look for all the classes of entities that are also archeological sites and tourist attractions?
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?name where{{ ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q570116 . ?entity wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }} limit 50

search_workflow.narrative: let's try with archeological site and culture, see if the classes that we find are relevant for point 2
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?name where{{ ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?entity wdt:P2596 ?culture . ?entity wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }} limit 50

search_workflow.narrative: let's see instead the superclasses of the classes that we are retrieving
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?super ?name where{{ ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?entity wdt:P2596 ?culture . ?entity wdt:P31 ?class . ?class wdt:P279 ?super . ?super <http://schema.org/name> ?name }} limit 50

select distinct ?super ?name where{{ ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q570116 . ?entity wdt:P2596 ?culture . ?entity wdt:P31 ?class . ?class wdt:P279 ?super . ?super <http://schema.org/name> ?name }} limit 50

search_workflow.narrative:
let's see the top 50 most common types
get all of the types
search_workflow.query: select ?super ?name (count(*) as ?n) where{{ ?super <http://schema.org/name> ?name . {{ select ?super where{{ ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q570116 . ?entity wdt:P2596 ?culture . ?entity wdt:P31 ?class . ?class wdt:P279 ?super . }} }} }} group by ?super ?name order by desc(?n) limit 50

select ?super ?name (count(?super) as ?n) where{{ ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?entity wdt:P31 ?class . ?class wdt:P279 ?super . ?super <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }} group by ?super ?name order by desc(?n) limit 50

search_workflow.narrative: let's try in another way, without superclasses
search_workflow.query: select ?class ?name (count(?class) as ?n) where{{ ?entity wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?entity wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }} group by ?class ?name order by desc(?n) limit 50

search_workflow.narrative: Point 3. let's retrieve numerical properties for archeological sites
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 . ?site ?property ?o . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter(isNumeric(?o)) }} limit 100

search_workflow.narrative: let's rank the top 10 most visited sites in italy
search_workflow.query: select ?site ?name ?visitors where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1174 ?visitors . }} order by desc(?visitors) limit 10

search_workflow.narrative: i accidentally forgot to add italy, but colosseum is still the most visited each year
search_workflow.query: select ?site ?name ?visitors where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1174 ?visitors ; wdt:P17 wd:Q38 . }} order by desc(?visitors) limit 10

search_workflow.narrative:
we still only get the colosseum...
let's see the most visited site for each continent
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?continentName ?name ?visitors where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1174 ?visitors ; wdt:P17 ?country . ?country wdt:P30 ?continent . ?continent <http://schema.org/name> ?continentName filter (?visitors = ?max) . {{ select distinct ?continent (max(?visitors) as ?max) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 ?country ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1174 ?visitors . ?country wdt:P30 ?continent . }} group by ?continent }} }}

search_workflow.narrative: this is suspicious, let's see just the max
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?continent (max(?visitors) as ?max) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 ?country ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1174 ?visitors . ?country wdt:P30 ?continent . }} group by ?continent

search_workflow.narrative: let's rank archeological sites by elevation
search_workflow.query: select ?siteName ?elevation where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName ; wdt:P2044 ?elevation . }} order by desc(?elevation) limit 10

search_workflow.narrative: let's rank cultures by the number of visitors the respective sites get each year
search_workflow.query: select ?cultureName (sum(?visitors) as ?total) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P1174 ?visitors ; wdt:P2596 ?culture . ?culture <http://schema.org/name> ?cultureName . }} group by ?cultureName order by desc(?total) limit 10

search_workflow.narrative: Point 4.1 which country has more archaeological sites? which country has the most human settlements?
search_workflow.query: select ?countryName (count(?site) as ?n) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 ?country . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . }} group by ?countryName order by desc(?n) limit 20

search_workflow.narrative: the united kingdom has more archaeological sites
search_workflow.query: select ?countryName (count(?site) as ?n) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q486972 ; wdt:P17 ?country . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName }} group by ?countryName order by desc(?n) limit 20

search_workflow.narrative:
spain has the most human settlements
4.2 Which countries have Ancient Rome sites? Which other archaeological cultures are described?
We have the node Ancient Rome, let's see its classes
search_workflow.query: select ?class ?name where{{ wd:Q1747689 wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}

search_workflow.narrative: for now let's answer the first part
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?country ?name where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P2596 wd:Q1747689 ; wdt:P17 ?country . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}

search_workflow.narrative: there's a few countries that look like dissolved, let's see if we have a dissolution time as a property
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ wd:Q185103 ?property ?p . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter (isNumeric(?p)) }}
select distinct ?property ?name where{{ wd:Q185103 ?property ?p . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}
output: located in the administrative territorial entity

search_workflow.query: select distinct ?country ?name where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P2596 wd:Q1747689 ; wdt:P17 ?country . filter not exists{{ ?country wdt:P576 ?o }} ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
4.2 which other archaeological cultures are described?
let's list all archaeological cultures in italy
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?culture ?name where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P2596 ?culture ; wdt:P17 wd:Q38 . ?culture <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}
output: history of the Roman Empire from 27 BCE to 395 AD

search_workflow.narrative: let's do that for Egypt
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?culture ?name where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P2596 ?culture ; wdt:P17 wd:Q79 . ?culture <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}

search_workflow.narrative: in which countries are Ancient Rome sites predominant?
search_workflow.query: select ?country ?countryName where{{ ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . {{ select ?country ?culture (max(?n) as ?max) where{{ {{ select ?country ?culture (count(?culture) as ?n) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 ?country ; wdt:P2596 ?culture . }} group by ?country ?culture }} }} group by ?country ?culture }} filter(?culture = wd:Q1747689) }}

search_workflow.narrative: should have also added filtered out dissolved countries but there's not too many
search_workflow.query: select ?culture ?name (count(*) as ?n) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 wd:Q183 ; wdt:P2596 ?culture . ?culture <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }} group by ?culture ?name order by desc(?n)
output: history of the Roman Empire from 27 BCE to 395 AD

search_workflow.narrative: 4.3 Which country has the most diverse set of civilizations or cultures across its sites?
search_workflow.query: select ?countryName (count(?culture) as ?n) where{{ ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName {{ select distinct ?country ?culture where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 ?country ; wdt:P2596 ?culture . }} }} }} order by desc(?n) limit(1)

search_workflow.narrative: let's do top 10
search_workflow.query: select ?countryName (count(?culture) as ?n) where{{ ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName {{ select distinct ?country ?culture where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 ?country ; wdt:P2596 ?culture . }} }} }} order by desc(?n) limit(10)

search_workflow.narrative:
4.4 Let's explore archaeological sites that are also tourist attractions
first of all let's figure out what the 2 properties 'fee' and 'cost' that we found earlier mean
search_workflow.query: select ?siteName ?fee where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q570116 ; wdt:P17 wd:Q38 ; wdt:P2555 ?fee ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName . }} order by desc(?fee) limit 20

search_workflow.narrative: let's try with cost
search_workflow.query: select ?siteName ?cost where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P31 wd:Q570116 ; wdt:P17 wd:Q38 ; wdt:P2130 ?cost ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName . }} order by desc(?fee) limit 20

search_workflow.narrative: let's retry without the Attraction class
search_workflow.query: select ?siteName ?fee where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 wd:Q38 ; wdt:P2555 ?fee ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName . }} order by desc(?fee) limit 20
select ?siteName ?cost where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 wd:Q38 ; wdt:P2130 ?cost ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName . }} order by desc(?cost) limit 20

search_workflow.narrative: let's try and ignore the country
search_workflow.query: select ?siteName ?fee where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P2555 ?fee ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName . }} order by desc(?fee) limit 20
select ?siteName ?cost where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P2130 ?cost ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName . }} order by desc(?cost) limit 20

search_workflow.narrative:
my hope was that one between cost or fee would indicate the price of entry into a site, unfortunately there's too few
sites with those properties so we can't use them to decide the country with the most affordable sites to visit
let's see if archeological sites have social media followers
search_workflow.query: select ?siteName ?n where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?siteName ; wdt:P8687 ?n }} order by desc(?n) limit 50

search_workflow.narrative:
archeological sites with many social media followers are also probably well organized for tourists, so that list would be useful
during this period of time, it's important to follow safety regulations, so the higher the capacity of a site, the better
search_workflow.query: select ?name ?cap where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1083 ?cap . }} order by desc(?cap) limit 50

search_workflow.narrative:
if we had information about capacity for more sites, we could combine it with the number of visitors each year
and pick archaeological sites that each year don't see too many visitors
search_workflow.query: select ?name ?visitors where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1174 ?visitors . }} order by desc(?visitors) limit 50
output: Temple of Poseidon at cape Sounion
Temple of Poseidon at cape Sounion
Temple of Poseidon at cape Sounion

search_workflow.narrative: let's only pick 1 entry for visitors for each site
search_workflow.query: select ?name (max(?visitors) as ?max) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1174 ?visitors . }} group by ?name order by desc(?max) limit 50
output: Temple of Poseidon at cape Sounion

search_workflow.narrative:
let's find the "best" country for each culture, meaning the country with most sites for each culture
count number of sites for each culture in each country
search_workflow.query: select ?countryName ?cultureName ?max where{{ ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . ?culture <http://schema.org/name> ?cultureName . {{ select ?country ?culture (count(?site) as ?n) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 ?country ; wdt:P2596 ?culture . }} group by ?country ?culture }} {{ select ?culture2 (max(?n2) as ?max) where{{ {{ select ?country2 ?culture2 (count(?site) as ?n2) where{{ ?site wdt:P31 wd:Q839954 ; wdt:P17 ?country2 ; wdt:P2596 ?culture2 . }} group by ?country2 ?culture2 }} }} group by ?culture2 }} filter(?culture = ?culture2 && ?n = ?max) }} order by desc(?max) asc(?cultureName) limit 50
output: history of the Roman Empire from 27 BCE to 395 AD
